 Hence,
 we have 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{P}_{\delta}-x^{*}=\frac{\delta}{\eta}(\mathcal{P}_{\eta}-x^{*})$
\end_inset

.
 Since 
\begin_inset Formula $x\in\mathcal{P}_{\delta}$
\end_inset

,
 we have that 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\|x-x^{*}\|_{2}\leq\frac{\delta}{\eta}\text{diameter}(\mathcal{P}_{\eta}-x^{*})\leq\frac{2\delta R}{\eta}.
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

