 every step,
 we first aim at 
\begin_inset Formula $xs=0$
\end_inset

 (called affine direction).
 Then,
 we check if we can take a large step on this affine direction.
 This is used to evaluation how long step size 
\begin_inset Formula $h$
\end_inset

 we can take.
 Finally,
 we compute a second order update step.
\end_layout

